## Python

```python
# Option 1: Using the range() function
numbers_array = list(range(1, 11))

# Option 2: Using list comprehension
numbers_array = [num for num in range(1, 11)]
```

## JavaScript

```javascript
// Option 1: Using the Array constructor and a loop
const numbers_array = Array.from({ length: 10 }, (_, i) => i + 1);

// Option 2: Using Array.from and a range function (requires polyfill)
const numbers_array = Array.from({ length: 10 }, (_, i) => i + range(1, 11)[i]);
```

## C++

```cpp
#include <vector>

std::vector<int> numbers_array;

for (int i = 1; i <= 10; ++i) {
  numbers_array.push_back(i);
}
```

## Java

```java
List<Integer> numbers_array = new ArrayList<>();

for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
  numbers_array.add(i);
}
```

These code snippets demonstrate how to create an array containing the numbers from 1 to 10 in different programming languages. The most common approaches involve using a loop or list comprehension to iterate over the desired range and add each number to the array.
